@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<style>
    .shell {
        max-width: 1220px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px 16px 30px;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .hero {
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 26px;
        background: radial-gradient(760px 280px at 15% 0%, rgba(79,70,229,0.16), transparent 58%), radial-gradient(560px 240px at 92% 18%, rgba(37,99,235,0.10), transparent 54%), linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-strong), var(--surface));
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
        padding: 22px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
        gap: 16px;
        align-items: center;
    }

    h1 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 30px;
        letter-spacing: -0.7px;
        font-weight: 950;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .sub {
        margin-top: 8px;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-weight: 750;
        font-size: 13px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 62ch;
    }

    .hero-pills {
        display: flex;
        gap: 10px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 14px;
    }

    .hero-pill {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        padding: 7px 11px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.20);
        background: var(--surface-tint);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 850;
        font-size: 12px;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

        .hero-pill.good {
            border-color: rgba(21, 128, 61, 0.18);
            background: var(--good-soft);
            color: var(--good);
        }

    .actions {
        display: flex;
        gap: 10px;
        justify-content: flex-end;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .btn {
        border-radius: 12px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
        background: var(--surface);
        color: var(--text);
        padding: 11px 14px;
        font-weight: 900;
        cursor: pointer;
        white-space: nowrap;
        text-decoration: none;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 8px;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
        transition: transform .12s ease, background .12s ease, border .12s ease, box-shadow .12s ease;
    }

        .btn:hover {
            transform: translateY(-1px);
            background: var(--surface-soft);
            border-color: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.24);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
        }

        .btn.primary {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), #6366f1);
            border-color: transparent;
            color: #ffffff;
        }

    .topStats {
        margin-top: 16px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 12px;
    }

    .stat {
        border-radius: 18px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-strong), var(--surface-soft));
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
        padding: 14px;
    }

        .stat .k {
            color: var(--muted2);
            font-weight: 850;
            font-size: 11px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: .3px;
        }

        .stat .v {
            color: var(--text);
            font-weight: 950;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        .stat .s {
            color: var(--muted);
            font-weight: 750;
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-top: 4px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

    .grid {
        margin-top: 16px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
        gap: 14px;
    }

    .card {
        border-radius: 22px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-strong), var(--surface-soft));
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
        padding: 18px;
    }

        .card h2 {
            margin: 0 0 10px;
            font-size: 17px;
            font-weight: 950;
            letter-spacing: -0.25px;
            color: var(--text);
        }

    .hint {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-weight: 750;
        font-size: 12px;
        line-height: 1.65;
        margin-top: -2px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 10px;
    }

    .item {
        display: flex;
        gap: 10px;
        align-items: flex-start;
        padding: 12px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: var(--surface);
    }

        .item input {
            margin-top: 4px;
            transform: scale(1.1);
            accent-color: var(--accent);
        }

        .item .t {
            font-weight: 900;
            color: var(--text);
            font-size: 13px;
        }

        .item .p {
            margin-top: 4px;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-weight: 750;
            font-size: 12px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

    .pillRow {
        display: flex;
        gap: 10px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 12px;
    }

    .pill {
        padding: 7px 10px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: var(--surface);
        color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 850;
        font-size: 12px;
    }

        .pill.good {
            border-color: rgba(21, 128, 61, 0.18);
            background: var(--good-soft);
            color: var(--good);
        }

        .pill.warn {
            border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.20);
            background: var(--warn-soft);
            color: var(--warn);
        }

        .pill.bad {
            border-color: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.18);
            background: var(--bad-soft);
            color: var(--bad);
        }

    details {
        margin-top: 12px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: var(--surface);
        padding: 12px 14px;
    }

        details summary {
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: 950;
            color: var(--text);
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            gap: 12px;
        }

            details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
                display: none;
            }

            details summary::after {
                content: "+";
                font-size: 18px;
                font-weight: 900;
                color: var(--accent);
            }

        details[open] summary::after {
            content: "–";
        }

        details .content {
            margin-top: 12px;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-weight: 750;
            font-size: 12px;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

    .links a {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 900;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

        .links a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
            color: var(--accent-hover);
        }

    .noteBox {
        margin-top: 14px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.16);
        background: var(--surface-tint);
        padding: 12px 14px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 800;
        line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .miniSection {
        margin-top: 14px;
        padding-top: 12px;
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(100, 116, 139, 0.16);
    }

    .miniTitle {
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 950;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .print-report {
        display: none;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 980px) {
        .hero {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .actions {
            justify-content: flex-start;
        }

        .grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .topStats {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }

    /* ================= PRINT ONLY ================= */
    @@media print {
        @@page {
            size: A4;
            margin: 12mm;
        }

        html, body {
            background: #ffffff !important;
            color: #111827 !important;
            height: auto !important;
            overflow: visible !important;
            -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
            print-color-adjust: exact;
        }

        .screen-view {
            display: none !important;
        }

        .print-report {
            display: block !important;
            width: 100% !important;
            color: #111827 !important;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

            .print-report h1 {
                font-size: 26px !important;
                margin: 0 0 6px 0 !important;
                color: #111827 !important;
            }

            .print-report .report-date {
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #6b7280;
                margin-bottom: 16px;
            }

            .print-report .report-sub {
                font-size: 13px;
                line-height: 1.7;
                margin-bottom: 16px;
                color: #374151;
            }

        .print-section {
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            page-break-inside: avoid;
        }

            .print-section h2 {
                font-size: 18px;
                margin: 0 0 8px 0;
                color: #111827;
                border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db;
                padding-bottom: 6px;
            }

            .print-section ul {
                margin: 0;
                padding-left: 18px;
            }

            .print-section li {
                margin-bottom: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
                color: #374151;
            }

        .print-note {
            border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
            background: #f9fafb;
            padding: 10px 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #374151;
        }

        .print-links div {
            margin-bottom: 6px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .print-links a {
            color: #111827 !important;
            text-decoration: underline !important;
        }
    }
</style>

<div class="shell">
    <div class="screen-view">
        <section class="hero">
            <div>
                <h1>Tenant Checklist</h1>
                <div class="sub">
                    A practical checklist to help you move from “Shortlist results” to “sign the lease” with confidence.
                    Use this page during searches, viewings, and applications so you do not miss anything important.
                </div>

                <div class="hero-pills">
                    <span class="hero-pill">Viewing prep</span>
                    <span class="hero-pill good">Scam awareness</span>
                    <span class="hero-pill">Lease readiness</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="actions">
                <button class="btn primary" type="button" onclick="window.print()">Print / Save PDF</button>
                <a class="btn" href="/Results">Back to Results</a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="topStats">
            <div class="stat">
                <div class="k">Step 1</div>
                <div class="v">Screen the listing</div>
                <div class="s">Check price, address, landlord communication, and obvious red flags.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
                <div class="k">Step 2</div>
                <div class="v">Inspect carefully</div>
                <div class="s">Use the checklist during the viewing so details are not missed.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
                <div class="k">Step 3</div>
                <div class="v">Document everything</div>
                <div class="s">Keep receipts, copies, photos, and written confirmations.</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Before you book a viewing</h2>
                <div class="hint">Goal: avoid scams and filter out weak listings early.</div>

                <div class="list">
                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">Confirm the address is real</div>
                            <div class="p">Search the address, compare listing photos, and check whether the same photos appear on unrelated websites.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">Ask basic questions in writing</div>
                            <div class="p">Confirm rent, utilities, parking, move-in date, lease term, deposits, and application requirements before visiting.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">Do not pay before viewing</div>
                            <div class="p">A legitimate landlord or property manager should provide a viewing and proper documentation before asking for money.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="noteBox">
                    Tip: Save screenshots of the original listing before it changes or disappears.
                </div>

                <details open>
                    <summary>Viewing checklist (what to check on-site)</summary>
                    <div class="content">
                        <div class="list">
                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Water pressure and hot water</div>
                                    <div class="p">Test sinks and shower, check how quickly hot water arrives, and look for leaks underneath.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Windows, locks, and phone signal</div>
                                    <div class="p">Open and close windows, test locks, and check phone signal if you rely on mobile data indoors.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Noise level</div>
                                    <div class="p">Listen for traffic, hallways, neighbors, building systems, and nearby construction noise.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Heating, cooling, and ventilation</div>
                                    <div class="p">Ask how temperature is controlled and whether the tenant or building manages it.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details open>
                    <summary>Application package (what to prepare)</summary>
                    <div class="content">
                        <div class="list">
                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Proof of income</div>
                                    <div class="p">Prepare pay stubs, an offer letter, or limited supporting documents only if reasonably requested.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">References</div>
                                    <div class="p">Keep previous landlord, roommate, or employer references ready if the application process asks for them.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">ID and safe document sharing</div>
                                    <div class="p">Bring ID in person, but avoid sending unnecessary sensitive records unless truly required.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details open>
                    <summary>Lease signing (do not skip these)</summary>
                    <div class="content">
                        <div class="list">
                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Read the lease carefully</div>
                                    <div class="p">Review rent amount, included utilities, lease term, parking, maintenance responsibility, and building rules.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Keep receipts and signed copies</div>
                                    <div class="p">Save payment confirmations, lease copies, emails, and any move-in documents.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="item">
                                <input type="checkbox" />
                                <div>
                                    <div class="t">Take move-in condition photos</div>
                                    <div class="p">Photograph walls, appliances, floors, and damage on day one to prevent later disputes.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Scam red flags</h2>
                <div class="hint">If you notice multiple red flags together, it is safer to walk away.</div>

                <div class="pillRow">
                    <span class="pill bad">Money before viewing</span>
                    <span class="pill bad">Pressure / urgency</span>
                    <span class="pill warn">Unverified identity</span>
                    <span class="pill warn">Too-good-to-be-true price</span>
                    <span class="pill bad">No lease / no paperwork</span>
                </div>

                <div class="list" style="margin-top:12px;">
                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">They refuse to show the unit</div>
                            <div class="p">Excuses like “I’m out of the country” combined with a deposit request are common warning signs.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">They ask for unusual payment methods</div>
                            <div class="p">Gift cards, crypto, wire transfers, or personal transfer arrangements are high-risk.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="item">
                        <input type="checkbox" />
                        <div>
                            <div class="t">Important details keep changing</div>
                            <div class="p">The address, rent, included utilities, or move-in date changes after you ask follow-up questions.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="miniSection">
                    <div class="miniTitle">Good practice during communication</div>
                    <div class="list">
                        <div class="item">
                            <input type="checkbox" />
                            <div>
                                <div class="t">Keep messages in writing</div>
                                <div class="p">Email or platform messages are easier to reference later than phone-only conversations.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="item">
                            <input type="checkbox" />
                            <div>
                                <div class="t">Bring someone to the viewing if possible</div>
                                <div class="p">A second person can notice issues you miss and adds confidence during the visit.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <details open class="links">
                    <summary>Helpful links (Ontario)</summary>
                    <div class="content">
                        <div>• Landlord and Tenant Board (LTB): <a href="https://tribunalsontario.ca/ltb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tribunalsontario.ca/ltb</a></div>
                        <div>• Ontario Standard Lease guide: <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/guide-ontarios-standard-lease" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ontario.ca/page/guide-ontarios-standard-lease</a></div>
                        <div>• Tenant rights overview: <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/renting-ontario-your-rights" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ontario.ca/page/renting-ontario-your-rights</a></div>
                    </div>
                </details>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div class="print-report">
        <h1>Shortlist – Tenant Checklist Report</h1>
        <div class="report-date">Generated on: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy hh:mm tt")</div>
        <div class="report-sub">
            A practical checklist to help you move from “Shortlist results” to “sign the lease” with confidence.
            Use this page during searches, viewings, and applications so you do not miss anything important.
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Before you book a viewing</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Confirm the address is real:</strong> Search the address, compare listing photos, and check whether the same photos appear on unrelated websites.</li>
                <li><strong>Ask basic questions in writing:</strong> Confirm rent, utilities, parking, move-in date, lease term, deposits, and application requirements before visiting.</li>
                <li><strong>Do not pay before viewing:</strong> A legitimate landlord or property manager should provide a viewing and proper documentation before asking for money.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="print-note">Tip: Save screenshots of the original listing before it changes or disappears.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Viewing checklist (what to check on-site)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Water pressure and hot water:</strong> Test sinks and shower, check how quickly hot water arrives, and look for leaks underneath.</li>
                <li><strong>Windows, locks, and phone signal:</strong> Open and close windows, test locks, and check phone signal if you rely on mobile data indoors.</li>
                <li><strong>Noise level:</strong> Listen for traffic, hallways, neighbors, building systems, and nearby construction noise.</li>
                <li><strong>Heating, cooling, and ventilation:</strong> Ask how temperature is controlled and whether the tenant or building manages it.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Application package (what to prepare)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Proof of income:</strong> Prepare pay stubs, an offer letter, or limited supporting documents only if reasonably requested.</li>
                <li><strong>References:</strong> Keep previous landlord, roommate, or employer references ready if the application process asks for them.</li>
                <li><strong>ID and safe document sharing:</strong> Bring ID in person, but avoid sending unnecessary sensitive records unless truly required.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Lease signing (do not skip these)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Read the lease carefully:</strong> Review rent amount, included utilities, lease term, parking, maintenance responsibility, and building rules.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep receipts and signed copies:</strong> Save payment confirmations, lease copies, emails, and any move-in documents.</li>
                <li><strong>Take move-in condition photos:</strong> Photograph walls, appliances, floors, and damage on day one to prevent later disputes.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Scam red flags</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Money before viewing</li>
                <li>Pressure or urgency</li>
                <li>Unverified identity</li>
                <li>Too-good-to-be-true price</li>
                <li>No lease or no paperwork</li>
                <li>Refusal to show the unit before payment</li>
                <li>Unusual payment methods such as gift cards, crypto, or wire transfers</li>
                <li>Important listing details keep changing</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section">
            <h2>Good practice during communication</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Keep messages in writing for easier reference later.</li>
                <li>Bring someone to the viewing if possible.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="print-section print-links">
            <h2>Helpful links (Ontario)</h2>
            <div>Landlord and Tenant Board (LTB): <a href="https://tribunalsontario.ca/ltb/">tribunalsontario.ca/ltb</a></div>
            <div>Ontario Standard Lease guide: <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/guide-ontarios-standard-lease">ontario.ca/page/guide-ontarios-standard-lease</a></div>
            <div>Tenant rights overview: <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/renting-ontario-your-rights">ontario.ca/page/renting-ontario-your-rights</a></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>